00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:40.450
So one of the other
cool properties of eggs,

00:12:40.450 --> 00:12:44.740
in particularly egg yolks is
that they contain lecithin.

00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:47.810
Lecithin is an emulsifier.

00:12:47.810 --> 00:12:50.300
And I don't know how many of
you are familiar with what

00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:52.216
an emulsion is, but an
emulsion is essentially

00:12:52.216 --> 00:12:55.560
when you take two liquids
that are immiscible

00:12:55.560 --> 00:13:00.600
and force them to mix.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:03.640
In cooking it's almost
always a water-based liquid

00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:04.900
and a fat-based liquid.

00:13:04.900 --> 00:13:06.830
So like a traditional
vinaigrette,

00:13:06.830 --> 00:13:08.420
which we'll make it a bit.

00:13:08.420 --> 00:13:09.980
A butter is an emulsion.

00:13:09.980 --> 00:13:14.480
There's water in there, there's
about-- off the top of my head

00:13:14.480 --> 00:13:18.780
if I'm right, I think it's like
15% water and about 80% fat

00:13:18.780 --> 00:13:22.799
and a few other
percents of protein.

00:13:22.799 --> 00:13:24.340
And then what we're
going to make now

00:13:24.340 --> 00:13:27.540
is mayonnaise and hollandaise
which are both emulsions.

00:13:27.540 --> 00:13:30.780
They're both fat
in water emotions.

00:13:30.780 --> 00:13:34.380
Now in order to get
things to emulsify,

00:13:34.380 --> 00:13:37.170
what you need is a lot of
mechanical stirring first

00:13:37.170 --> 00:13:40.070
of all, and then
also an emulsifier.

00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:43.340
An emulsifier is
any sort of agent

00:13:43.340 --> 00:13:46.670
that has one hydrophobic
end and one hydrophilic end.

00:13:46.670 --> 00:13:49.190
So essentially what
you're doing is

00:13:49.190 --> 00:13:51.240
you're taking your
tiny droplets of fat

00:13:51.240 --> 00:13:53.670
or your tiny droplets
of water surrounding it

00:13:53.670 --> 00:13:55.710
on all sides with emulsifiers.

00:13:55.710 --> 00:14:01.760
So if you think of them as like
little sperm going into an egg,

00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:04.090
they got their heads
jammed in there.

00:14:04.090 --> 00:14:06.610
So if you have a fat molecule
all the hydrophilic ends

00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:08.300
are jammed into the
fat molecule, which

00:14:08.300 --> 00:14:13.060
leaves the exterior hydrophobic,
which makes it-- or did

00:14:13.060 --> 00:14:14.160
I reverse that?

00:14:14.160 --> 00:14:15.070
I reversed it.

00:14:15.070 --> 00:14:16.350
Anyhow, you know what I mean.

00:14:16.350 --> 00:14:18.475
So it makes it so that
those fat molecules can then

00:14:18.475 --> 00:14:20.520
be evenly distributed in water.

00:14:25.720 --> 00:14:28.780
The way you traditionally
would make a mayonnaise

