Hollandaise is one
of these sauces

00:22:40.230 --> 00:22:44.280
that is, again, like the bane
of a lot of brunch cooks'

00:22:44.280 --> 00:22:45.089
existence.

00:22:45.089 --> 00:22:46.880
It has all the difficulties
of a mayonnaise

00:22:46.880 --> 00:22:49.380
getting proper emulsion
to form, all of that.

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:52.900
Plus it's also very
temperature sensitive.

00:22:52.900 --> 00:22:57.830
If it gets too cool-- butter is
a highly saturated fat, which

00:22:57.830 --> 00:22:59.880
means that-- I
don't know if you're

00:22:59.880 --> 00:23:02.070
familiar with the shape
of a fat molecule,

00:23:02.070 --> 00:23:04.600
but it basically
looks like an e.

00:23:04.600 --> 00:23:06.794
Like it's got one-- what is it?

00:23:06.794 --> 00:23:08.210
Three fatty acids
and a glyceride.

00:23:08.210 --> 00:23:11.700
It's got a glyceride chain and
fatty acids sticking out of it.

00:23:11.700 --> 00:23:15.750
Those fatty acids they
have kinks in them

00:23:15.750 --> 00:23:18.690
based on how saturated or
unsaturated that the fat is.

00:23:18.690 --> 00:23:20.230
So when it's fully
saturated that

00:23:20.230 --> 00:23:22.910
means that every single
location on that fatty acid

00:23:22.910 --> 00:23:25.108
has a carbon.

00:23:25.108 --> 00:23:26.112
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:23:26.112 --> 00:23:27.320
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT: Hydrogen?

00:23:27.320 --> 00:23:28.615
Hydrogen. Yes, thank you.

00:23:28.615 --> 00:23:32.120
It has hydrogen on it, which
makes the legs straight.

00:23:32.120 --> 00:23:33.890
When it is missing
some of those hydrogens

00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:35.510
those legs end up kinking.

00:23:35.510 --> 00:23:39.580
So when you have a non
fully saturated fat

00:23:39.580 --> 00:23:41.330
it has kinked legs,
which means that it

00:23:41.330 --> 00:23:42.840
doesn't stack very easily.

00:23:42.840 --> 00:23:45.540
The molecules don't
pack very tightly.

00:23:45.540 --> 00:23:48.850
So highly saturated
fats like butter--

00:23:48.850 --> 00:23:51.180
tend to come from animals--
butter, beef fat, pork fat,

00:23:51.180 --> 00:23:53.980
duck fat-- you'll find that
because they stack so nicely

00:23:53.980 --> 00:23:55.480
they are solids at
room temperature.

00:23:58.570 --> 00:24:01.440
So obviously you can't make
mayonnaise out of a solid.

00:24:01.440 --> 00:24:05.740
So hollandaise is difficult,
because if the butter fat gets

00:24:05.740 --> 00:24:07.130
too cool, it becomes a solid.

00:24:07.130 --> 00:24:08.910
It breaks out of its emulsion.

00:24:08.910 --> 00:24:12.142
But if it gets too hot, you
end up cooking the egg yolks.

00:24:12.142 --> 00:24:13.600
So it's really this
balancing game,

00:24:13.600 --> 00:24:17.940
but when you use this method it
solves a lot of those problems,

00:24:17.940 --> 00:24:19.070
again.

