00:25:18.740 --> 00:25:20.450
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT:
Well, so a you

00:25:20.450 --> 00:25:21.500
don't want to make
pesto in the blender,

00:25:21.500 --> 00:25:23.333
because it's not the
best way to get flavor.

00:25:23.333 --> 00:25:26.940
You want to make pesto it
in a mortar and pestle.

00:25:26.940 --> 00:25:28.850
You rupture a lot more.

00:25:28.850 --> 00:25:30.950
So a blender is
actually too violent.

00:25:30.950 --> 00:25:32.480
And it's too sharp.

00:25:32.480 --> 00:25:35.780
So it'll separate plant
cells at their walls.

00:25:35.780 --> 00:25:38.790
So you actually don't extract
as much flavor-- thank you--

00:25:38.790 --> 00:25:40.281
when you blend like basil.

00:25:40.281 --> 00:25:42.030
You don't extract as
much flavor out of it

00:25:42.030 --> 00:25:44.814
as you do when you really grind
it in a mortar and pestle.

00:25:44.814 --> 00:25:46.230
When you make your
pesto, you want

00:25:46.230 --> 00:25:50.316
to get a nice granite
mortar and pestle.

00:25:50.316 --> 00:25:51.940
And this is one of
the rare cases where

00:25:51.940 --> 00:25:53.481
the really old
fashioned way actually

00:25:53.481 --> 00:25:55.262
is the best way to do it.

00:25:55.262 --> 00:25:56.970
You want a grand and
mortar pestle, salt,

00:25:56.970 --> 00:25:58.386
which is also an
abrasive and will

00:25:58.386 --> 00:25:59.700
help you break it down more.

00:25:59.700 --> 00:26:01.450
And that'll make
it better pesto.

00:26:01.450 --> 00:26:02.962
But to answer your
initial question,

00:26:02.962 --> 00:26:05.420
if you are going to make your
pesto in a blender and a food

00:26:05.420 --> 00:26:08.410
