00:31:40.450 --> 00:31:42.870
So again, making a vinaigrette
the traditional way

00:31:42.870 --> 00:31:45.040
is actually very similar
to making a mayonnaise.

00:31:45.040 --> 00:31:49.490
You start with your acid, maybe
a little bit of mustard, maybe

00:31:49.490 --> 00:31:51.890
a shallot or two in a bowl.

00:31:51.890 --> 00:31:54.440
Start whisking it and then
slowly drizzle in your oil.

00:31:54.440 --> 00:31:55.970
And you end up with an emulsion.

00:31:55.970 --> 00:31:57.940
Because there's no
lecithin in there

00:31:57.940 --> 00:32:01.500
the emulsion is not quite as
strong as it is in mayonnaise.

00:32:01.500 --> 00:32:05.090
And that's why mayonnaise
is so thick and gloppy,

00:32:05.090 --> 00:32:07.960
whereas a vinaigrette
is loose and creamy.

00:32:07.960 --> 00:32:13.050
