J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT: Mustard.

00:34:59.030 --> 00:34:59.430
Mustard.

00:34:59.430 --> 00:34:59.870
Yeah.

00:34:59.870 --> 00:35:00.370
Yeah.

00:35:00.370 --> 00:35:02.300
But mustard is not as
strong as lecithin,

00:35:02.300 --> 00:35:08.367
which is why it doesn't really
hold the emulsion as well.

00:35:08.367 --> 00:35:10.075
You know, and even
without an emulsifier,

00:35:10.075 --> 00:35:13.670
it's possible to get like a
relatively loose emulsion.

00:35:13.670 --> 00:35:15.290
But it'll eventually separate.

00:35:15.290 --> 00:35:17.020
But this one you see,
it's pretty creamy.

00:35:20.790 --> 00:35:24.770
So this one we're going to
also throw some salad greens.

00:35:36.438 --> 00:35:38.422
I'm adding a couple
tablespoons of this.

00:35:43.382 --> 00:35:45.000
Toss them all together.

00:35:48.690 --> 00:35:52.760
And where did I put
that clean bowl?

00:35:52.760 --> 00:35:56.255
Did I lose my last clean bowl?

00:35:56.255 --> 00:35:57.722
Let's go with this bowl.

00:36:03.090 --> 00:36:03.590
OK.

00:36:07.030 --> 00:36:07.540
OK.

00:36:07.540 --> 00:36:08.960
There we go.

00:36:08.960 --> 00:36:10.960
And hopefully this is
actually going to work out

00:36:10.960 --> 00:36:12.120
the way it's supposed to.

00:36:15.220 --> 00:36:16.210
Sometimes it does.

00:36:16.210 --> 00:36:19.080
All right, so this
one is tossed with oil

00:36:19.080 --> 00:36:24.500
and you can see like basically
nothing drips into the bowl.

00:36:24.500 --> 00:36:29.654
And that's because leaves
have this kind of natural waxy

00:36:29.654 --> 00:36:31.820
coating on them so that
when they're out in the rain

00:36:31.820 --> 00:36:35.660
the rain just rolls off of them
instead of soaking into them.

00:36:35.660 --> 00:36:39.690
So oil actually binds
really well to salad greens

00:36:39.690 --> 00:36:41.190
and to leaves of all kinds.

00:36:41.190 --> 00:36:45.310
And actually if you've seen your
salad green start to go limp,

00:36:45.310 --> 00:36:46.910
it's the oil that's doing it.

00:36:46.910 --> 00:36:47.730
It's not the acid.

00:36:47.730 --> 00:36:48.450
It's not the water.

00:36:48.450 --> 00:36:48.991
It's the oil.

00:36:48.991 --> 00:36:51.440
So you can see like here it's
already starting to go limp

00:36:51.440 --> 00:36:53.648
and that's because the oil
is soaking into the leaves

00:36:53.648 --> 00:36:55.180
and saturating the cells.

00:36:55.180 --> 00:36:56.880
So no dripping from oil.

00:36:56.880 --> 00:36:58.987
So it's good because the
oil sticks to the leaves

00:36:58.987 --> 00:37:00.820
and that's where you
want it, because that's

00:37:00.820 --> 00:37:02.403
where you get the
flavor, but it's bad

00:37:02.403 --> 00:37:05.140
because it ruins your greens.

00:37:05.140 --> 00:37:07.550
Now we go to the
one with the acid

00:37:07.550 --> 00:37:10.460
and this is the one
that I hope worked.

00:37:10.460 --> 00:37:14.444
And imagine that the bowl has
a lot of stuff down there.

00:37:14.444 --> 00:37:15.860
JENNA TAYLOR: Tons,
tons of stuff.

00:37:15.860 --> 00:37:18.193
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT: If we had
it sit a little bit longer

00:37:18.193 --> 00:37:20.264
you would have probably seen it.

00:37:20.264 --> 00:37:21.930
Or if this thing had
bigger holes in it.

00:37:21.930 --> 00:37:24.179
Oh, yeah, it's all pulling
at the bottom of the thing.

00:37:24.179 --> 00:37:28.260
Anyhow, your acid basically
it just runs off the leaves,

00:37:28.260 --> 00:37:29.830
it doesn't really stick to them.

00:37:29.830 --> 00:37:33.060
And that's bad, because you
need that bright acidity to make

00:37:33.060 --> 00:37:34.860
your salad taste good.

00:37:34.860 --> 00:37:37.670
So the point of a vinaigrette
is that you get your acid in oil

00:37:37.670 --> 00:37:39.290
to play nicely together.

00:37:39.290 --> 00:37:43.161
And then here again no drippage.

00:37:43.161 --> 00:37:45.410
It coats the leaves nicely,
but now coating the leaves

00:37:45.410 --> 00:37:46.752
is oil plus acid.

00:37:46.752 --> 00:37:48.460
So you get the flavor
from the olive oil,

00:37:48.460 --> 00:37:50.510
you also get the
flavor from the acid.

00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:54.180
The leaves are protected
from the effects of the oil,

00:37:54.180 --> 00:37:56.181
because of that
water-based element.

00:37:56.181 --> 00:37:58.430
And so that's the reason why
you want to actually form

00:37:58.430 --> 00:38:01.440
a really nice tight vinaigrette
and not just haphazardly throw

00:38:01.440 --> 00:38:02.460
things on your salad.

00:38:02.460 --> 00:38:03.835
And it's also why
it doesn't work

00:38:03.835 --> 00:38:06.570
to just kind of add extra
vinegar at the table

00:38:06.570 --> 00:38:07.120
or whatever.

00:38:07.120 --> 00:38:08.870
You need to really
make a nice vinaigrette

00:38:08.870 --> 00:38:10.380
if you want a nice salad.

00:38:10.380 --> 00:38:12.940
Actually I had a really nice
