00:40:53.343 --> 00:40:54.718
AUDIENCE: In the
first part where

00:40:54.718 --> 00:40:57.134
you were poaching the eggs,
was the water at a mild simmer

00:40:57.134 --> 00:40:57.870
at the lowest--

00:40:57.870 --> 00:41:00.670
JENNA TAYLOR: What's the
temp of the eggs or the water

00:41:00.670 --> 00:41:01.990
when you're poaching the eggs?

00:41:01.990 --> 00:41:03.200
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT:
It was below a simmer.

00:41:03.200 --> 00:41:05.670
So the main reason I like
to keep it below a simmer

00:41:05.670 --> 00:41:07.160
is actually just a physical one.

00:41:07.160 --> 00:41:09.493
I don't want the bubbles
coming up there and interfering

00:41:09.493 --> 00:41:11.630
with the eggs and jostling
them around too much.

00:41:11.630 --> 00:41:13.170
Partly I also don't
want the metal

00:41:13.170 --> 00:41:14.590
at the bottom of the
pan to be too hot.

00:41:14.590 --> 00:41:16.250
So ideally when I
poach eggs what I do

00:41:16.250 --> 00:41:18.710
is I get like a
rather large pot.

00:41:18.710 --> 00:41:20.745
I'll bring it to a boil
then I'll shut it off.

00:41:20.745 --> 00:41:22.120
And then I'll add
the eggs to it.

00:41:22.120 --> 00:41:25.510
So the water
temperature is probably

00:41:25.510 --> 00:41:30.940
above 180 degrees, below 200
degrees, around that range.

00:41:30.940 --> 00:41:33.330
JENNA TAYLOR: What temp
should the eggs themselves be?

00:41:33.330 --> 00:41:36.960
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT: So,
OK, that's a good question.

00:41:36.960 --> 00:41:40.350
So I actually like to use
fridge cold eggs for poaching.

00:41:40.350 --> 00:41:42.950
And the main reason is
that those tight whites

00:41:42.950 --> 00:41:45.360
and tight yolks are actually
more viscous when they're

00:41:45.360 --> 00:41:47.110
cold from the fridge
so it makes it easier

00:41:47.110 --> 00:41:48.780
to do that straining step.

00:41:48.780 --> 00:41:51.782
If they come all the
way to room temperature,

00:41:51.782 --> 00:41:53.240
especially with
slightly older eggs

00:41:53.240 --> 00:41:54.730
there's a small
chance that doing

00:41:54.730 --> 00:41:57.010
that step you're going
to end up breaking

00:41:57.010 --> 00:41:59.070
the shell, the membrane
around the white

00:41:59.070 --> 00:42:00.944
and you definitely don't
want that to happen.

00:42:00.944 --> 00:42:03.980
So I like to use fridge
cold eggs for poaching.

