00:43:04.160 --> 00:43:04.945
Worked out.

00:43:04.945 --> 00:43:05.820
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

00:43:05.820 --> 00:43:07.570
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT:
Yeah, well vinaigrette

00:43:07.570 --> 00:43:09.880
is a very good example of that.

00:43:09.880 --> 00:43:12.250
I use one part
water-based liquid,

00:43:12.250 --> 00:43:16.150
so that could be lemon juice,
vinegar, and then three parts

00:43:16.150 --> 00:43:17.190
oil.

00:43:17.190 --> 00:43:20.765
And then about maybe up to
one part in addition to that.

00:43:20.765 --> 00:43:22.140
The liquids you
can do by volume,

00:43:22.140 --> 00:43:26.120
but one part by weight
of additional aromatic.

00:43:26.120 --> 00:43:28.470
So it can be garlic,
it can be shallots,

00:43:28.470 --> 00:43:32.742
it can be some kind of
barbecue spice blend,

00:43:32.742 --> 00:43:34.700
powdered ranch dressing
mix, whatever you want.

00:43:34.700 --> 00:43:37.900
But yeah a vinaigrette you want
a three to one ratio of oil

00:43:37.900 --> 00:43:38.520
to water.

00:43:38.520 --> 00:43:39.490
That's a good one.

00:43:39.490 --> 00:43:42.780
I would actually recommend
