That way you're making
sure that people are really

00:55:37.843 --> 00:55:40.120
using their ears and
their eyes and that's

00:55:40.120 --> 00:55:42.030
how you should be cooking.

00:55:42.030 --> 00:55:45.410
Use a timer, use a
thermometer, but always

00:55:45.410 --> 00:55:48.220
time things first with
your eyes, and your ears,

00:55:48.220 --> 00:55:49.819
and your nose, and your fingers.

00:55:49.819 --> 00:55:51.610
JENNA TAYLOR: Who eats
all of the leftovers

00:55:51.610 --> 00:55:53.470
from your experiments?

00:55:53.470 --> 00:55:56.590
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT:
So sometimes my wife.

00:55:56.590 --> 00:55:59.300
It depends on if it's a
recipe she likes or not.

00:55:59.300 --> 00:56:01.430
And if it's a recipe she
likes, by the end of it

00:56:01.430 --> 00:56:04.100
it's a recipe she
hates, because she'll

00:56:04.100 --> 00:56:07.570
eat boiled eggs for
three weeks straight.

00:56:07.570 --> 00:56:09.450
Sometimes it's my wife.

00:56:09.450 --> 00:56:11.570
When I lived in New York,
