00:56:13.950 --> 00:56:17.030
I would take it into the office,
my neighbors, my doorman.

00:56:17.030 --> 00:56:19.490
Now we live in San Mateo
next to a family that

00:56:19.490 --> 00:56:23.550
has three kids, two kids, and
so they get a lot of our food.

00:56:23.550 --> 00:56:25.720
The dogs get a lot of food, too.

00:56:25.720 --> 00:56:29.480
The dogs had wagyu steak for
breakfast couple weeks ago.

00:56:29.480 --> 00:56:30.554
Lucky.

00:56:30.554 --> 00:56:32.220
JENNA TAYLOR: What's
your favorite thing

00:56:32.220 --> 00:56:34.550
to order when you eat out?

00:56:34.550 --> 00:56:36.841
J. KENJI LOPEZ-ALT: It depends
what kind of restaurant.

00:56:36.841 --> 00:56:40.180
So if it's like your
typical California cuisine--

00:56:40.180 --> 00:56:41.280
I mean, vegetables.

00:56:41.280 --> 00:56:43.860
I order vegetables and
fish when I eat out.

00:56:43.860 --> 00:56:47.490
I think, if you're going to
a really high end restaurant

00:56:47.490 --> 00:56:50.990
or even like a really
nice mid range restaurant,

00:56:50.990 --> 00:56:54.120
I think the two best dishes
to judge a restaurant on

00:56:54.120 --> 00:56:55.970
are actually generally
the most boring,

00:56:55.970 --> 00:57:00.110
so I think it's a
salad and the chicken.

00:57:00.110 --> 00:57:02.470
And those two things if
they can do it right,

00:57:02.470 --> 00:57:05.240
those things are oftentimes
they're almost afterthoughts.

00:57:05.240 --> 00:57:07.340
They're things like oh we have
to have a salad and a chicken.

00:57:07.340 --> 00:57:09.280
But if they show care and
attention when they're

00:57:09.280 --> 00:57:11.410
doing that, and perfectly
cooked chicken, I think,

00:57:11.410 --> 00:57:13.360
could be amazingly tasty.

00:57:13.360 --> 00:57:15.220
And a really perfectly
dressed salad

00:57:15.220 --> 00:57:17.111
with a properly made
vinaigrette, well

00:57:17.111 --> 00:57:19.610
balanced ingredients, that can
also be really, really tasty.

00:57:19.610 --> 00:57:21.660
So if a restaurant does
those two things right

00:57:21.660 --> 00:57:25.431
then I'm pretty sure that they
care about everything else.

00:57:25.431 --> 00:57:26.430
JENNA TAYLOR: Wonderful.

00:57:26.430 --> 00:57:28.270
Thank you so much.

00:57:28.270 --> 00:57:31.920
[APPLAUSE]

